Essar Telecom Kenya Head Steps Down; Will Be Replaced by Taneja

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-04T06:45:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/essar-telecom-kenya-head-steps-down-will-be-replaced-by-taneja.html
Essar Telecom Kenya Ltd.  Country
Manager  Atul Chaturvedi  said he will step down and be replaced
by Madhur Taneja, the chief executive officer of  Warid Telecom 
in neighboring  Uganda .  Chaturvedi will be “moving out of an executive role” at
Essar Kenya, known as yu, he said in a phone interview today
from Nairobi, the capital.  Chaturvedi is the third person to head Essar Communications
Holdings Ltd’s Kenyan unit, the East African nation’s fourth-
biggest mobile company, since it began operations in November
2008. Taneja will replace Chaturvedi in March, the Nairobi-based
 Daily Nation  reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at   eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 